article.description: Bill Wampler came off the bench to score 18 points to carry Wright State to a 71-56 win over IUPUI in the quarterfinals of the Horizon Conference Tournament on Tuesday night.
article.headline: Wright State tops IUPUI 71-56 in Horizon tourney
article.linkText: Wright State tops IUPUI 71-56 in Horizon tourney
article.story: DAYTON, Ohio -- Bill Wampler came off the bench to score 18 points to carry Wright State to a 71-56 win over IUPUI in the quarterfinals of the Horizon Conference Tournament on Tuesday night. Wampler made 4 of 6 3-pointers. Loudon Love had 13 points and nine rebounds for Wright State (20-12). Skyelar Potter added 12 points. Malachi Smith had 11 points for the home team. Jaylen Minnett had 17 points for the Jaguars (16-16). D.J. McCall added six rebounds. Ahmed Ismail had three blocks. Camron Justice was held to only 8 points. The Jaguars' leading scorer entering the contest at 19 points per game, he failed to make a shot from behind the arc (0 of 4). --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
